launchpopup.text: This tool helps an agent to analyze which jobs and occupations have high risks of accidental injury or death and create an insurance plan for the client accordingly. It provides a risk rating and a detailed description of the substances, tools, and chemicals that can be hazardous for the clients at their workplace.

desktopdata.text: Occupation Exposure Advisor tool helps agents analyze which jobs and occupations are exposed to risks, so that they can prepare a beneficial solution for the client.
Click the LAUNCH button on the home screen to launch the tool.
To select an occupation, click the search icon.
Type the name of the occupation in the search bar.
You can also scroll through the list and click an occupation to select it.
Once you select an occupation, select the Duties Code pertaining to that occupation.
If an occupation has only one Duties Code, that Duties Code is selected by default.
Click ASSESS RISK to view the risk report related to the chosen occupation.
Here’s the risk report. It provides a risk rating and a detailed list of the hazards related to the occupation.
You can scroll down to view the entire report.
The generated report can be printed and shared through various modalities based on the device it is viewed on.
To assess risk for another occupation, click RESET.
